The paper discusses exploring the prediction level sets of a classifier using probabilistic programming, which is a common topic in the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on neural networks, which falls under the sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the robustness and generalization ability of neural networks, which are topics in the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE) and cryptography (cs.CR), respectively.
